                                                   Akhtar likely to sit out

           
	Karachi: Shoaib Akhtar is likely to sit out the upcoming one-day series against Zimbabwe. PCB chairman Nasim Ashraf has laid down a clear policy to the selectors and team management that no player should be selected unless he proves his 100 per cent match fitness, a well-informed source said. 
    
	The board was disappointed at Shoaibs fitness in India... now all the players who have had fitness issues in recent times will only be picked after they prove their match fitness, he said. 
    
	The ODI series starts January 21. (PTI) 
                                                   
